content: This app is really great! I love that I can keep up with multiple people's average. My husband and I go bowling at least once a week and I store all of our game totals so I know what our average is at all times. My major complaint is that once I start tracking our games for the night, it doesn't allow me to look at any other games, like if I wanted to see my scores for a previous night, I would have to exit my session and start all over. Other than that, it's great! It was still worth buying.
Very easy to use and packed with a lot of helpful features for such a low price!
I hate it. And I PAID for it!!!

content: Great!

I love this app so much. totally worth it. i also appreciate how you are always improving it and being open to feedback. Great App!!!
Excellent tool for keeping track of everything bowling.

I did 12 test games with this. It worked great! There is 1 suggestion that I have, however. Add a digit separator to values with 4 or more digits (example: cumulative score across all games, which, for me, is currently 1,765). I observed the absence of a digit grouping in that value.

More stats the better, and it calculates the scores correctly, which I would think would be the minimum requirement for a bowling app, however some others that are out there bug out and mess totals up, especially when you adjust a prior frame. Definitely worth the few bucks for premium, one of the few apps I feel good paying for

Far and away the best score/record keeping app I've used for bowling. The continued updates and newer versions are a bonus. I happily pay for this app because of it's continued support and improvements and useful, detailed statistics.

Very easy to use and gives great insights into that spares you leave most often, your hit percentages. Also keeps you motivated, especially if you start a game off bad. For example, i started a game with two open frames. In the past I'd get frustrated and the game would be horrible. Instead the app shows your max score and i realized i could still shoot mid 200. In the past it would have turned into a 150 game instead i went on to finish with a 212
